BEIJING, Nov. 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are the central parity rates of the Chinese currency renminbi, or the yuan, against 24 major currencies announced on Wednesday by the China Foreign Exchange Trade System: Currency Unit Central parity rate in yuan U.S. dollar 100 639.48 Euro 100 741.28 Japanese yen 100 5.6628 Hong Kong dollar 100 82.088 British pound 100 866.93 Australian dollar 100 471.49 New Zealand dollar 100 455.47 Singapore dollar 100 474.59 Swiss franc 100 701.80 Canadian dollar 100 514.11 Malaysian ringgit 64.888 100 Ruble 1,106.20 100 Rand 235.37 100 Korean won 18,448 100 UAE dirham 57.44 100 Saudi riyal 58.653 100 Hungarian forint 4,864.25 100 Polish zloty 61.935 100 Danish krone 100.33 100 Swedish krona 134.12 100 Norwegian krone 133.04 100 Turkish lira 152.187 100 Mexican peso 317.83 100 Thai baht 512.45 100 The central parity rate of the yuan against the U.S. dollar is based on a weighted average of prices offered by market makers before the opening of the interbank market each business day. The central parity rate of the yuan against the Hong Kong dollar is based on the central parity rate of the yuan against the U.S. dollar and the exchange rate of the Hong Kong dollar against the U.S. dollar at 9 a.m. in international foreign exchange markets on the same business day. The central parity rates of the yuan against the other 22 currencies are based on the average prices offered by market makers before the opening of the interbank foreign exchange market. Enditem